# Crucible Console — local configuration. Copy to `console/.env` (gitignored).
# The Console is a view/remote-control over a Crucible consumer repo; it holds no
# state itself. EVERYTHING HERE IS OPTIONAL — with `gh` and `claude` already set up
# on your machine, the Console needs no .env at all (beyond pointing at a repo).

# The Crucible consumer repo the Console operates on (default: current directory).
CRUCIBLE_REPO=/absolute/path/to/your-crucible-project

# GitHub token. If unset, the Console REUSES YOUR `gh` CLI LOGIN (`gh auth token`),
# so you usually don't need this. Set it only to override or if `gh` isn't installed.
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxx

# Claude subscription token for the spec-drafting chat. If unset, the Console uses
# your logged-in host `claude` CLI directly. One token works across ALL your projects
# (it's tied to your Claude account, not a repo). Mint with `claude setup-token`.
# CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=sk-ant-oat-xxx

# Optional: server port (default 7317).
# CONSOLE_PORT=7317
